pr_body:
Example: `http://localhost:8080/alerts?api-key=demo-key&limit=50&page=1&service=foo`

```
{
  status: "ok",
  total: 1,
  pageSize: 50,
  statusCounts: {
    closed: 1
  },
  alerts: [ ... ],
  page: 1,
  more: false,
  severityCounts: {
    normal: 1
  },
  lastTime: "2014-12-21T11:49:52.024Z",
  pages: 1,
  autoRefresh: true
}
```

The errors list is accessed via ``request.errors``, it makes thus no sense to store a circular reference.

And «Look mum, no tests fail!» (*ie. no spec was changed*)

@Natim r?

THIS IS NOT AT ALL READY TO MERGE

@robinandeer have a look at the build hgnc gene file, there are some suggestions there of how this migration could be handled.
Parse just parses but build makes sure that the database is consistent.
